list.name: Default
list.comment: - added exporter progress bar - added kv6 export

task.summary: Default task
- made JPCT multi threaded - set minimal JVM heap size to 512
- before "only asyn essentials"
- fixed asyn action manager problem that caused the worker thread to die
- added bounding box - minor changes / removed some debug code

- reduced input lag (by ~50ms!) - "full repaint" is no longer executed when fast draw overview calls are happening (reduced load when not actually changing the scene) - collision detection is now much faster (gosh, recoloring huge objects is now sooo much faster!) - layout loading from XML file now, much easier to add changes - decreased checks on start-up (if not in debug mode) - added an option bar (will probably remove the selection-interaction bar - there are too many buttons) - added mirror tool - fixed one problem with the RTree (but pretty sure there is more...) - fixed a deadlock problem (which I had previously overseen, hopefully last one)
- added /study command for console
- "good code practice" fixes - added new class that deals with streams (and closing) - improved cross platform compatibility - and more
- added flood fill
- made flood fill a separate tool - prettified message for shortcuts clashing when not in debug mode
- added recolor functionality to flood fill tool
- improved texture and color repaint (doesn't re-add the voxel anymore) - fixed "black flashing rectangles" on startup - color changer right click is not "color picker" - some minor fixes
- changed how max polygon count is assigned (to allow less polygons for sides, but more for main view)

- got rid of all the uses of RTree - vsd file size reduction - side view only uses one layer selection now - side view only shows appropriate side (instead of all) of the voxel - changed voxel position access (to use less int[3].clone()) to reduce load on gc (this will reduce micro stutter)
- finished migration to blackflux.com - added some basic information/help
- major restructuring of tool logic
- added profiler (to see what takes how long)
- significantly reduced triangle count - fixed bug where the selection in the sideview could get stuck - removed lots of unnecessary code - lots and lots of restructuring

- fixed "do you want to save?" query appearing when loaded project was not changed - fixed potential synchronization problem (multi threading problem) - fixed "snap to voxel" not working (animation mode) - fixed bug were rotated/flipped textures (images projected onto voxel faces) were displayed incorrectly - fixed bug were selection was not refreshing when changing between animation and voxel mode - fixed bug were textures were not rotated in the correct direction when exporting to COLLADA - increased max zoom distance for main and side view

- significant code optimization and memory reduction - saved files are now smaller - collada exporter is now a little bit faster - selection of huge objects is now faster (more optimization is still planned) - loading of projects is now faster - removed lots of unnecessary code
- changed rotation method for buffered image (better memory efficiency)
- fixed a bug that resulted in stuck faces inside of geometry - separated the test for the CubeIndexer
- some synchronization fixes - jpct warnings only shown in debug mode
- heavy restructuring of the file/folder names in the project (this will break the pref.ser)
- restructuring (package renaming) - started working on new core for storing voxels - toggle for low/high rendering quality - delete now stays in plane when dragging (draw right click and erase tool)

- software edge detection experiments - fixed old format to file loading - fixed mouse1 and mouse3 pressed at the same time issue in draw mode - removed 9x9 grid lines (except for textures) - high quality defaults to true
- areas that only require a texture refresh are no longer fully refreshed
- when modifying an area (shift key), the dimension of the area is shown in the right top corner
- new jpct version - sync fixes - added camera and voxel test modes - minor fixes/optimization
- fixed lag when drawing first voxel after startup (warmup)
- bug fix: voxel selection update shouldn't trigger texture refresh of neighbouring plane areas (areaID)
- added color palette window - some minor fixes - centralized file loader logic
- neighbours can now also be reached with WASD even if blanks are in between
- fix highlighting bug when changing tools while hovering mouse over draw area - added confirm message when color palette export is overwriting file
- added splash screen - fixed null pointer exceptions (2x) - optimized color palette window (full redraw only when necessary)
- splash screen update (alpha) - alt now also enables camera - alt is no longer activates the window menu - compilation again with jdk 1.6 (instead of jdk 1.7)
- slider now stretches with window width (color slider window) - text input area now is a bit smaller (color slider window)
- added support for updating the updater
- fixed bug where textures were not unloaded when "clearing" the world

- minor optimization - centralized hash computation for BufferedImage - fixed bug where unknown texture id was used for drawing after closing a texture project - textures can now be non-quadratic - textures are now only loaded if an equivalent texture doesn't exist - added command to show how many textures are loaded and the size they occupy in memory - fixed a bug where voxel sides could get stuck when using several layers

- possible texture images are now pre-buffered again (some where missing b/c didn't consider non-square) - fixed a bug where the CWorld.clear() wasn't synchronizing correctly and could cause concurrent modification error in rare cases - added a new jpct version that fixed a bug that caused objects not to display available textures - added version number to splash screen - separated title string from version number
- added binvox importer - changed how layer visibility changing works - added "all files" (std selected) when opening files (so all files with appropriate endings are displayed)
- centralized file loading and saving logic (so all importer and exporter can use it)
- added support for importing (animated) gifs as voxel
- centralized all voxel format file importer - added importer for *.kv6 - added importer for *.kvx
- added importer for *.qb - import layer name now uses the file name
- fixed checking/loading problem with (old?) kv6 files - added tests for easily checking import of many files for supported import formats
- fixed bug where voxel side did contain the wrong voxel -> this caused a problem with multiple layers and overlapping voxel
- fixed kvx importer (color values were read incorrectly)
- fixed issue with kv6 importer (voxel were added double) - added support for *.vox (MagicaVoxel) and *.vox (Voxlap Engine) - slightly restructured import logic
- added *.vox loading (config and voxel file) for vox-game.com - fixed another problem with loading defect kv6 files
- restructured file dialog logic to allow for multiple file extensions in one filter entry - added support for *.bmp import

- added naive greedy meshing algorithm for triangulation - added monotone meshing algorithm for triangulation with option for 2D safe triangulation - wrote own implementation of voxel -> polygon with holes that is much faster - /study now outputs results of different algorithms for triangulation

- added "/shader" option for enabling/disabling shader - fixed outline shader to be more robust and faster - added optimal greedy meshing method with tests - restructured meshing algorithms and tests (removed redundant code)
- fixed software shader to work with oversampling - added exporter for image and depth map - added dispose() for most created Graphics contexts
- added RawVox Importer - restructured importer logic

- added help overlay (glasspane) - bundled JTable related style information - bundled JScrollPane related style information - fixed bug that triggered a delayed focusevent when menu was closing - added functionality to find maximum rectangle in binary grid (currently unused) - fixed potential bug where null graphics object could have been accessed
- help overlay is now automatically displayed on the first three startups

- bounding box is not resizable - 2D side view is not truly orthogonal - fixed two small problems with the number input field - fixed problem with tool adapter (mouse event was replayed with deactivated adapter) - changed how the bounding box is drawn (more efficient and better looking) - centralized dynamic settings - fixed problem with split-item not showing popup when "checked" - reworked "offline" texture generation
- fixed point/line sorting of animation in side view (points are now always in front of lines) - fixed bug where animation point wasn't draggable directly after placing it

- started working on new COLLADA exporter - error message popup is no longer thrown if unable to load vsd file - added console msgs for import/load errors - fix: handle to files that didn't load/import is released correctly now
- added DDA supercover algorithm for lines and triangles
- progress: exporting textured triangles works now (each triangle has it's own texture image - compression is missing)

- progress: added texture compression (scaling textured down when doing so is loss less) - texture ids are now dynamic and assigned in a way to keep the "low" - added function to IntegerTools to detect all factors of an integer (not just prime factors)
- progress: added texture reduction (textures are checked for containment and only not contained textures are used)
- progress: improved texture compression (this variant uses UV modification to compress "inside" areas) - progress: only one texture file is generated (however not arranged yet)
- fixed rounding problem with COLLADA exporter - some minor alterations/improvements - progress: textures are now combined (still needs more work)

- fixed conceptual problem with texture compression (points were not translated correctly!) - added method to find intersecting grid cells when points are arbitrary and not between four grid cells (for line and triangle) - sped up triangle comparison by using trove hash maps - added test for texture compression - fixing further rounding problems with grid line intersection (when in between four grid cells, i.e. the int version) - significantly reduced memory usage when exporting
- minor fix for "point line" grid intersection
- progress: all orientations are now considered when assembling the final texture (optimization still needed) - area instead of pixel count is now used when ordering images before merging
- converted point queries to int queries
- code restructuring (removed some redundancy)
- fixed deadlock - added console method "/check deadlock": if enabled this checks periodically and dumps deadlock information to error file if deadlock found
- sorting by maximum dimension before merging textures into single texture
- added ray-casting collision detection (much faster for large objects) - added ray-triangle-hit-test function
- improved hit testing - fixed bug in cube indexer where generated ids were inconsistent
- improved hit testing (only visible sides are hit now) - added ms time to export message - slightly improved export speed (i.e. added sorting)
- added hull manager max box function for rays (origin of a ray is shifted into the bounding box if outside) - currently not necessary since the camera always lives in the max box

- fewer objects generated when testing ray collision - added function to hullManager to update positions by id (saves calculation!) - changed how the ghost overlay of "previous side plane" is calculated (uses highly efficient grid analysis algorithm now) - added method to hullManager to efficiently get outline of it's content (for one side)
- 3D t-junction problems are now fixed for the COLLADA export
- fixed: bug where side view rectangles would be drawn as "3D" (slight performance improvement, but mainly visual fix)
- optimization (using trove HashMap)
- added shortcut for import action (CTRL + SHIFT + E)

- added support for "place color axis at border of bounding box" (disabled though) - performance improvement when batch adding voxels (significant!) and selecting voxels - increased layer voxel limit to 100k - added "custom text field" that has a listener and can be restricted to specific characters
- finished dialog system (started in previous commit!)
- created a test dialog with necessary modules for export dialog - several dialog related fixes and improvements
- added serialization for dialog - some minor improvements to dialog
- dialog optimization
- fixed issue where combobox deserialization could cause an exception

- fixed small repaint bug (visual) for color palette - made floating windows borderless (press CTRL to adjust) - removed lots of unnecessary borders from sub-frames - dialog is no longer resizable by user
- floating frame border color now matches header (and changes when activated frame changes) - added "snap to gid"
- integrated exporter logic (initial) - some fixed/changed to dialog system
- minor adjustments - added "naive" exporter logic that exports two triangles per voxel face
- added progress bar - added strike through option for checkbox - integrated progress bar for import and export
- fixed buggy display when dragging floated windows (help system glass pane was interfering!)
- DockingManager no longer uses glass pane for mouse cursor changes (wasn't working anymore - since the help system modifies the glass pane??)
- fixed mac compatible issue with separators
- changed interpolation value
- added texture padding - started working on new design
- continued work on dark design
- minor border fixes
- added title bar closing, minimize, maximize buttons - fixed dbl click toggle maximize - minor layout changes/fixes
- fixed (hacked?) black border issue - changed console window input field color - minor layout related fixes/adjustments - custom icons for sub-frames
- added extraction/sorting/clear functionality for color palette
- added support for vox game format (vox-game.com)
- fixed that only current layer was considered when exporting (vox game format exporter)
- fixed cursor overlay not displaying correctly (glasspane problem)
- fixed bug in vox format where "," was used instead of "." for comma separation
- implemented hole removal - added "/study holes" command - added test for hole removal - moved extended hull manager logic to new class (with interface) - added wrapper function to cubeIndexer
- fixed bug in "remove caves" export - added fill and hollow function
- added exporter progress bar - added kv6 export
- fixed minor kv6 export bug
- added option for kv6 export (weighted center or origin)
